<tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#666699" align="center"><font size="3"><b>Hunting Guide for Levels 30 - 34</b></font></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="3" align="right" bgcolor="#eeeeee">&nbsp;<a href="/guides/submitHunting.asp?level=30">Submit New Hunting Guide</a></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Ak'Anon</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Town</font>|<font size="1">Tag=akanon</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Oftune Outtakey</b> (<i>1/21/02</i>) Kill gnomes here. invis in till you get to a safe spot with only mechanics and/or clockwork guards. exp is great and mobs can drop up to 30pp in items and 5pp cash. find the circle where you can kite multiple mobs for best exp. G'luck</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Butcherblock Mountains</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=butcher</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>songwriter</b> (<i>8/23/02</i>) Crazed goblins great xp got to lvl 39 off these things good luck</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Charmony</b> (<i>9/15/01</i>) Dwarves! Selo's (in walk mode) then just dot! Great exp. One whole blue per kill at lvl 33 (cons yellow at 33 and 34, even at 35) If you can grab a sow or if you have Jboots/Tboots all the easier. Only downside? I wish they spawned faster but its a nice camp...</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Castle Mistmoore</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=mistmoore</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Denbo</b> (<i>11/27/01</i>) This Zone is great to solo at this level range of 30-36.  Grab your flute and invs your self to the graveyard.  While in the graveyard stay on the right side and kill the single spawn.  do NOT FEAR kite.  Tank it it not to hard to tank.  I have 800 hp and I kill it with like 300hp left.  <br><br>Next break out the lute and rest to full.  there will be 2 spawns across and 2 more in front.  Lull and pull.  Nothing to hard here.  if you want you can charm one to beat on the other but I think it better to lull and take one at a time.  At times a caster will spawn there,  pretty easy to take out if you Mezz it non stop to prevent it from healing.<br><br>Note when a mob starts running besure to snare it.<br><br>Benifits of this zone,  <br>1) not camped to often<br>2) Black silk gloves for lambent quest drops<br>3) 13-20(Forget what it was) % exp bonus<br>4) Bard faction :)</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>3/26/01</i>) Most bards should spend a little time hunting here at some point. Two of our lower-level magical instruments drop here, plus there are quest items necessary for Lambent armor. And besides, Mayong Mistmoore is the enemy of the League of Antonican Bards!</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Cazic-Thule</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=cazicthule</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Yeawenette</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Cazic-Thule is a wonderful alternative to the outdoor soloing routine.  Between levels 30 and 34, you have several choices of places to group, and even solo if you're feeling adventurous.  Note that this is an outdoor zone, so Selo's is available if you run into trouble.<br><br>1. Gator Alley: This area, reached via the doorways above the entrance into the courtyard, contains roughly 15 alligators which will spawn between levels 20 and 30 and one rare spawn with placeholders that will spawn level 35 for the most part.  This is wonderful experience for a balanced level 30 group, and can be done, with difficulty by even a duo at level 34 or so.  Alligators, because they drop no loot to speak of, have an unusually high experience modifier.  Solo, you can try and charm down here, but adds during a break may make this a risky proposition.  The Steel Golem which is the rare, drops a piece of Ravenscale (rogue only armour) rarely.<br><br>2. The Sewers: This area, almost always camped, offers tremendous experience for a balanced group averaging their low 30s.  Alligators and the high level spawning lizards populate this area and multiple mob pulls are frequent.  Many of the lizards in this area (Judicators and Justicars) are clerics.  Additionally, Lizard Crusaders, which drop quest components for Darkforge (Shadowknight only armour) spawn here and are shadowknights and will Harm Touch your puller.<br><br>3. Throne Room #1:  This area offers roughly 15 or so lizard spawns and two hulking gorillas, along with the Tae Ew Templar rare and Tae Ew Diviner rare, which both drop a piece of Ravenscale (rogue only armour).  Action is almost always constant because of the sheer number of spawns, and can provide outstanding entertainment when you defeat that six or seven lizard battle.<br><br>4. Throne Room #2:  Usually only camped when TR1 is, there are more lizards and a Clay Golem rare with a Ravenscale rare drop, that spawn just behind the main throne room, which are, for the most part, a few levels higher than those in TR1.<br><br>5. Avatar of Fear: The &quot;boss&quot; of Cazic-Thule, a level 40 Shadowknight which is the god Cazic-Thule's incarnation on Norrath, lives in a green globe and has multiple lizard guards.  This area is good for a level 35ish group, and connects to the sewers, so lizards and alligators can be pulled from the sewers while the AoF room is empty.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Gilgurth</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) CT is an interesting place to hunt. If you go there earlier and hunt the entrance/courtyard/maze, you'll probably have to deal with some trains from the deeper areas. Also, as Whee pointed out, alot of the areas in CT will be fighting against multiples. With the recent changes to Pixie Strike, it is definitely possible to play crowd control in CT, and I would recommend it as a good learning grounds for such.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Crystal Caverns</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=crystalcav</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Lyrisa Nightingale</b> (<i>8/10/01</i>) 29-35 fight from the entrance of zone all the way down the ramp to the pit killing orcs. Many nooks to pull to and large strips to solo/charm kite. Great drops here crystalline belt and CC oracle cloak + many others.<br>35-40 Terrors and spiders .. Great experiance and bards are in high demand there. <br>35-45-Geonids... I know many of you are saying ack my geo faction. Did you know that Geonid faction goes up with time played. I've killed hundreds of them there. The geonids are at this point 3 levels from last time I killed one indifferant to me. They drop gems that sell to venders for 50-200pp and the xp is great.<br>Best part of this zone... there is a bank there! </span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>FlareX</b> (<i>7/20/01</i>) Crystal caverns is great for 28+ i was there at 30 and still am and it is great exp at the terrors they have mad exp and i mean MAD EXP if u go anon and just say a bard looking for a grp they dont care they will let you in and then the mad exp comes just try to help melee and chain song and charm the adds that is very helpfull the loot here is also mad (crystal covered shroud,blackened crystaline robe,stalagterror spear, and other items not to mention they drop 5pp a piece) this is great exp and there are also other areas in CC that are good exp also but i recoment the TERRORS!--FlareX MilleX-united guardians</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Kembas</b> (<i>5/17/01</i>) You can even start here at lvl 28. I was grouped with a monk and a cleric most of the time and the exp and loot was great. Plenty of safe spots to pull to/from.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Solo Charm kiting and groups</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Dalnir</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=dalnir</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Menvaren</b> (<i>4/18/01</i>) I've spent 28-30 hunting in Dalnir.  It's a fairly small dungeon, so a zone line isn't too far in case things get ugly.  There are a lot of casters, so oure resist songs are highly desired.  I've never had a problem finding a group; you'll generally end up grouping with monks because a lot of them go there for Crescent Armor.  Pull from outside the Temple or the &quot;L&quot; room where nothing aggros and xp flies.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Dawnshroud Peaks</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=dawnshroud</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Kinuven</b> (<i>7/31/02</i>) this place is pretty good for kiting the mushrooms, but the mushrooms hits hard = (<br><br>i am using fear/snare kiting here right now and its a blue per kill, for lvl 33<br><br>i have been kiting gnolls in south karana before i came here, gnolls aren't that good exp after like 30, i think DSP is a good place to kite stuff = )<br><br>Kinuven Soulchanter<br>Level 33 bard from Prexus</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Didju</b> (<i>7/18/02</i>) Charm kiting in Dawnshroud gives rocking XP.<br>First...go to Sanctus zone....follow the track out from there, picking up a wolf pet on the way. Wolves can take out higher conning Zelniaks, which give really sweet xp. <br><br>Avoid the area to the right as you come out of Sanctus, unless you like getting agroed by about 10 lightcrawlers as you bellow kite down your wolf ex-pet.<br><br>The mushrooms to the left as you come out of sanctus are pretty sweet too, 3 spawn there on a fairly fast timer.<br><br>Handy bind spot, shops and a bank in the next zone...what more could you ask for? well, maybe better loot, but that would be greedy :)<br><br>You can also pick up some of the parts for the twilight sea armour quests here (if you are in any way masochistic)<br><br></span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>East Karana</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=eastkarana</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>1/19/02</i>) Watch out for Proon, the daddy. Red to me at lvl 30 and almost wipped out my group, but we zoned before. (monk and druid). He arrived from the bridge.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>12/13/01</i>) Its Broon and Droon. Not the cyclops for our Lambent quest. Broon was blue and droon was yellow to my 28th bard. Good kitting experience, but get sow, its a lot faster then twisting selo. <br>Froon and Choon are found in WK, near the ogres. Those two you need for the quest and are higher lvl then Broon and Droon.<br><br>Tulamien Forestsong<br>Xev server<br></span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Threetall</b> (<i>7/19/01</i>) Think of it as an opportunity. If you are traveling thru and see Froon or Choon, look around for a griffawn. Charm the griff and have it beat on the cyclops. It will get him down to half before dying then its an easy kite from there. Bring them both by the bridge and you will have an appreciative audience. &quot;Wow, look at the bard get that griff to fight for him&quot;</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Tomias Wintersong</b> (<i>5/1/01</i>) Although, very easy... Charm kiting Froon and Choon isn't all that profitable for EXP or Loot. They have like a 20 minute spawn time, so that's a lot of waiting around. I like to hit them as I am running through the zone to Qeynos and then again on the way back.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Charm kiting Froon and Choon</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Eastern Wastes</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=ewastes</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Lulak</b> (<i>12/14/03</i>) I came here at level 30. I was on my way to Iceclad when I noticed some blue. And I also noticed a blue Rygorr scout. I then realized this place was a good source of money. First time I got in there I foudn a HQ Kodiac Pelt which sold for 350pp. I also found about 3 orc fang earrings, a frozen mantel, and other things that are worth some PP. PLus the exp is great. I normally switch back and fourth from fear kitting and charming (because i get bored if i do just one thing) But I also made great exp, im lvl 31 now and still killing, very close to level 32<br><br>-Lanolwen 31st Bard</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Profundo Basso</b> (<i>8/22/02</i>) At level 33 or 34.  Once the Frost Giants in Iceclad turn blue, head to Eastern Wastes.  <br>Remember to change your bind point from the dock at IC to Thurg.  Once you are across the bridge, take a right (north).  Go past the orc camp and leave them alone.  There's a mystic that will be a major pain if you try and kite the whole camp.  He'll SoW the biggest centurion orc, who will chase you down and eat your lunch.  Skip them and continue until you see the herd of Wooly Rhinos.  They should con yellow or red to you, perfect for charm kiting.  There are Ulthorks too, but you could be generous and leave those to the lv 40 druids that are always working on them.  <br><br>Rhinos are slow and there are a bunch of them, perfect for charm kiting.  Pick a yellow one and sic him on a red.  When your pet is down to 15% health, chant him to death.  Find another yellow rhino and repeat.  Think of the red con rhino as the anvil that you are bashing the yellows against.  When the red is down to 10%, chant him.  Don't try this without a good charm hotkey setup.  You will get your ass handed to you if you can't keep Selo's up and your pet targetted.<br><br>The loot is ... basically ... nothing.  But I went from 33 to 35 in 5 hours.  <br><br>Since you're there, kill those pesky Ulthorks too.  Walrus tusks and Ulthork hide armor.  Velium weapons.  Try for the yellow cons, won't resist much, but good exp.  Swarm kiting these is SO much easier than cougars.  They run like molasses in January.  Zone to dump aggro if you confuse your pets and target the wrong mob.  IC zone line is closer and has better visibility.<br><br>What I didn't do was kill Coldains.  Everyone else in my guild has Giant faction except me.  They sell Coldain heads for lots o' plat.  If I understood the faction implications better, I'd have advice on that subject.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Kludark</b> (<i>10/3/01</i>) Yes,  I was grouped with a 43 druid at Ry'Gorr fort and got mint exp at 30 by playing mana during downtime and helping mezz so she could medd.  They also drop about 4pp each and common Velium weapons.  Oh yea, and Ry'Gorr armor as well which is nice.<br><br>-Kludark</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Ruldar</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) On a side note, with the recent changes in the way exp is divided in a group (i.e. by level instead of by exp needed to level), if you want to level fast try to get into higher level groups fighting stuff thats red to you. I went through 30 in no time fighting with some of my higher level friends in the Queen room in CC and the Ry'Gorrs in EW. Got some good loot there too.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Gilgurth</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Keep on charm kiting. Seems like Velious was made for a charm kiting bard!</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Solo Charm kiting and Groups</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Estate of Unrest</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=unrest</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Reed Stormwind</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) I flew through 29-33 in the Ghost room in Unrest(and still no DWB's, grr). The catch was to be in a group that had at least one person who knew what they were doing, and 5 others who knew to listen to him. If you have that, exp runs quickly. If you don't have that, exp runs AWAY quickly. Some notes:<br>(1) Clear your way down the hall, and after you've established yourselves in the ghost room, keep the hall cleared.<br>(2) Always keep your backs against a wall (ie, not to the pit) when fighting a tentacle or dark terror.<br>(3) Go all-out nuke on the hags. Clerics stunning is nice... bards should prolly either repeatedly strike or twist anti-magic songs (or charming them is fun, too).<br>(4) Snare/Chain EVERYTHING.<br>(5) Never fall into the pit. If you need to catch a runner, go out the hall exit, not the pit walkway exit. If you've snared/chained it and it's on the walkway, nuke/dot it dead... running onto the platform risks accidentally falling into the pit.<br>(6) Druids in wolf form are not KOS'd... let them take a look to see what's around.<br>(7) There is a single mob spawn point in the little passage that goes from the main room to the ghost room. Root, stun, nuke quickly. Do not let him run, or you're going to have to deal with whatever is in the ghost room, also. Then, med up at the spawn point, and get ready for the ghost room assault. Go in with Clouding up, so everyone can get in position. (Charm or mez the TT/DT while the party drops the Ghost/hag. Then, mez the TT for a few minutes while your party rests up to break the room spawn.<br>(9) I've heard people say you have to clear the pit to (a) make the ghost spawn or (b) prevent the pit from coming up when something runs up the platform. This is false. Pulling the pit is only done for exp. If you use the passageway to chase runners instead of the platform, you don't even need to worry about the pit. (PS -- be careful when charming something against TT's... one almost threw my hag pet into the pit, and I'm not sure what that would have done).<br>(10) It's hard to get a good angle to Lament/Harmony the pit from the platforms above, but it can be done.<br>(11) Again, keep that hall clear between ghost spawns. You don't want to be running through mobs if you have a runner (and the ghost moves pretty well even when snared when he runs). Besides, it's all about exp... why miss any?</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Firiona Vie</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Town</font>|<font size="1">Tag=firiona</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Barnard</b> (<i>11/1/01</i>) well lots of people who have heard of the outpost here think the out post is the only thing here, that and the spiders on the way to loio.  well thats not the case.  there is a nice little temple to the east that is referred to as the dog temple.  great xp if you know what you are doing.  bard right?  well tell your group to bring the drovlargs to the side of the entrance of the temple.  once they are on the side, fear song fear song fear song, they run straight into the wall.  i had a group of 4 here, all were 30 to 32 and i, the bard of the group, sat there w/ my brass instrument fearing everything into the wall watching brass go up.  we were able to take on about 5 dogs at a time and i gained my lvl in less then 4 hours, and it was hell lvl 30 too.  try it, it works ;)</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Frontier Mountains</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Town</font>|<font size="1">Tag=frontier</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Tulamien</b> (<i>1/7/02</i>) Get a druid. Run in, grab 2 giants. Druid roots and dot one, you charm and send your pet on rooted giant. When dead, druid roots other giant and dot. If mana permits, run in to get another pet and repeat until out of mana. then just charm solo until druid is back to decent mana. Lots of fun and great loot. Plus the druid can port to sell those heavy weapons.<br><br>Tulamien Forestsong</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Fyion Vaisyas'Shan</b> (<i>12/11/01</i>) Yes this zone is crazy awsome for 30, just pull whatevert out to the south side and fear kite / dot kite in circles, if u pull 2- 3 just charm kite, very fun and exciting, have fun watching two giants go at it, hehe (note, giants r not mezzable, so dont try it =p )</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Gillan</b> (<i>10/8/01</i>) You can hold the giant fort solo with charm kiting, best pet is a tump it can beat 2-3 hillocks before needing 'retirement' and the flat area in front of the fort is a fairly safe place to kite. Even with a charisma of 105 they rarely resist. Even easier to do if you get a druid to sow you. Trouble is its fairly well camped but if you get on at a quiet time the place is yours....</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>8/4/01</i>) People who suggest going to Ill Omen Instead of FM are whacked. Although you will probably have to spend some actual real money (dollars not pp) and get a control pad. This aliviates stress from to much kiting and you don't have to run backwards anymore :). Just switch to a wide angle view and kite giants on relativly flat grounds (I prefer the north wall of the Giant fort). Experience is good, loot is good and soloing is easy. If you want be greedy and pull everything in the fort (long as your ping sustains it). I pulled 7 giants at 29, (including craig) and after 30minutes of charm kiting 1.5 yellow plus a heck of a lot richer. In a one hour span you can easily make 100-200pp (not counting loops) and tons of exp.<br><br>But the biggest note is to get a control pad and map your movement and song keys to it. Your hand will appreciate it in the long run no matter where you kite.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Britnee Golightly</b> (<i>6/26/01</i>) Blue giants (Hillocks and Tumps) are way too easy to bother with a group larger than 3.  Get a melee class (a monk for example) and some sort of healer (druid?) and go to work!  I found exp was best when I got an equal lvl melee class and MUCH lower lvl healer.  Between your healing song and mana songs, the healer stays good on mana, and the melee type takes most of the abuse during battle.  Fast exp!  If you do want a group of 6, focus on the craigs and braes.  Make sure you have a good puller though, its tough work to charm 2 or 3 consequtive braes while the rest of your group is getting battered.<br><br>Loot is GREAT!  You can make a huge amount of plat if you stay here a few hours.  I only saw one forest loop in many lvls of action here, but the 10 or 15 Giant Foreman's Tunics I sold for 64plat each to vendors makes up for it!<br><br>Another great activity for you in FM is corpse location.  Countless people get whacked while running through the confusing terrain and lose their corpses.  Help them out with your Locating Lyric!</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Tomias Wintersong</b> (<i>4/9/01</i>) Level 30 is a great time to start Giant fortress groups. Sit outside with a gorup of 4-6 and designate a puller. With a good group, pulls can begin immediately after a kill, so experience is always flowing. The Hillocks hit hard, but a gorup of melee people with Anthem/Chain going takes them down in 8-15 seconds.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Zamphir PanFlute</b> (<i>3/30/01</i>) Pull to the Overthere zone:  The valley there is incredibly long and provides and escape if things go wrong... Charm the Brutes, they hit hard and are really slow.  A bonecharmer = death. Engulfing Darkness, and a couple of spells and your toast, equip drum and outrun spells.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Charm kiting/Fear kiting in the corners</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Iceclad Ocean</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=iceclad</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>12/14/03</i>) You all talk about charm kitting... It is all about Denons! I pulled around 10 mobs, kitted them all in about 5 minutes and got at least 4 blues. (Level 31) I plan to keep repeating this, untill around lvl 33-34 i suppose... Just letting you know, Selos and Denons can be a great source of exp.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Johnei Bravo</b> (<i>11/22/03</i>) Obviously I'm not the first person to discover that cougars are 