ut not hitting you.  Now twist AE damage songs.  Cougars are very nice for this because they are quick and are easily hit by the AE spells)  You will find very quickly that you'll be able to take 3 yellow/low reds in about 20 minutes of kiting.  Please note you MUST Practice this on some blues somewhere else first... even greens or you will get slaughtered.  The other thing is you need a good link... lag will kill you and linkdeath will kill you.  It's risky but with a little practice you'll do well.  The key to this is practice ;)  Ok secondly Once you get your two cougar claw earrings (if you want) you can move on over to the bridge.  Charm kiting is an excellent means of exp.  Go find a yellow or lower frost giant set up a hotkey /pet attack a dire wolf (make sure you set the mob name exactly as it appears when you target it).  Next charm a giant point it at a dire wolf and get selo's up quick.  Stay back and watch the fun.  When either the giant or wolf start to walk away (after the charm breaks) run in big ol circles round them both and bellow the weak one to death (use amp here as well jacks your bellow dammage up about 20 levels ;) )  Full exp and ready to pull the next.  I've got it down now to the point where I can pull 5-6 giants 5-6 dire wolves and slaughter the mass of em.  Not bad for level 32 and good exp.  Just another way to apply the methods others teach.  Remember Bards, played right, are unstoppable.  Get used to handling and running around 30 things and nothing will shake you again after that :)  Best of luck to you all.<br><br>                                                       Overture InDMinor<br>                                                       Bard of the 34th song<br>                                                       Terris-Thule</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"> (<i>2/2/02</i>) Charm kitting cougars near the igloos at lvl 33. 1 yellow, 20 minutes. Loot is not very good, so I never stoped to loot. Every cougar I saw, I grabbed. Damn the ex is great. Oh, NO DOWNTIME. Not once in 2 hours of kitting. But had to stop as my head was spinning. So for breaks, i just twisted selo and charm, stop and let them fight, start running when charm broke, repeat charm. The only cougar i chant kitt was the last one. <br><br>Tulamien Forestsong</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Lanseril Darkbane</b> (<i>11/14/01</i>) Cougars!!!<br><br>I can't say enough how much EXP these little kities generate.  I explored around a little, and found my own private paradise.<br><br>2nd island, NE corner (near TOFS) there is a long empty space, with only rare wonderers.  The plan is this..and do this only if you are good at Charm kiting:<br><br>Locate the safe spot, right near the sea cliff, and then range out and look for prey.  I usually run around a bit ,and gather as many Cougars as possible..usually around 10.  Run back to the safe area, and pick any cougar out of the crowd.  Charm, hit F8, /pet attack, /pet target (so you don't lose your pet in the crowd) and watch the grp of cougars melt your pet.  You will be running from the ones that didn't agro your pet, but stay close to your pet, otherwise you wont get an accurate health count. Have Invis song up, and if it looks like you are going to lose your pet, invis, break charm, then bellow, or chant your former pet to death, then repeat.<br><br>Why swarm kite when you can just pull singles?  Swarming is much, MUCH faster.  Normal kiting takes about 4 charms before I have to finish them off.  Swarming takes 1-1.5 charms (1.5 = breaking charm with Invis) to nearly finish your pet.<br><br>I rarely got hit, and when I did I just twisted HYMN in a bit.  I went from 29-30 in about 2.5 hours.<br><br>Word of Warning...  Watch out for Midnight.  She is a named black cougar.  She spawns near the gnoll tent on occasion, adn from what i hear, she can really ruin your day.  I have always been able to avoid her, just be careful.<br><br>If you end up biting off more than you can chew, Equip your drum, and run from the safe area NE to the little iceberg bridge.  The cougars have never followed me that far.  camp out to clear agro, then start fresh.  Good luck.  <br><br>Lanseril Darkbane<br>Cult of Rathma<br>TORV</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Deafrude Izadork</b> (<i>8/5/01</i>) Exp here can be nuts like others have found it to be.  You can make 3+ levels here a day if you know what you are doing.  This is what I did in order to do that.  Just go to the Dragon Bridge and take a right.  That is where you will be pulling your mobs.<br><br>Find two wolves and one giant.  Make sure the giant is a red con.  Once pulled charm the giant and sick him onto the two wolves.  During the battle just keep Selo's up and keep your distance taking a beating from these things will equal death fast.<br><br>The giant will be able to finish off one wolf but you will need to help him take the other.  If you time everything right your last charm attempt should break just as both the second wolf and the giant are low HP.  They shouldn't even attack you at this state and should just walk away hurt.  Now your job is to just follow each around and finish the kill. <br><br>I was getting 2 blues each round of pulling.  Very fast exp but very dangerous also.  If you aren't very good at Charm Kiting this tactic isn't for you because you will die fast!<br><br>Goodluck fellow Bards.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Falshat</b> (<i>8/2/01</i>) I have been in Iceclad, 3rd Island for the last 2 levels, one of which was Hell 30.  Charming make the time fly by.  Just find a Frost Giant Scout and feast on anything that moves.  Once out of Hell, watching my exp bar making leaps and bounds was a welcome sight.  Stick to the water edge to avoid adds, and if you do get an aggro on you, just keep selo's going