ters.  Collect the spears (you can collect 36 of them weight free)  Sell to the dwarf on the mountain for about 7 gold (cha 123). 7 x 36 = 252 gold.<br><br>This is best XP since DW crocs, and not as much people KSing and being baby's over pulls.  You will be the only one there with your mage as your pet.<br><br>The only problem here is the boredom.  This is no Cazic Thule.  It is safe, slow and if things go bad, there is a zone about 3 seconds away. As long as you're mage is smart, you can literally keep mana song up and go AFK as LONG as you know when water stones run out<br><br>If things go bad,  high resist on charm's of all sorts.  DO not SOLONS.  It is your death due to stupid pathing problems.  Pixie is safer, but we all know about the high resist rate there ( thank you MR lowering nerf that caused Bards to DIE five million times)<br><br>Have fun.  Gain levels<br><br>Kyepez<br>32 Bard of Morell Thule<br><br><br>Kyepez plays a little Manilow<br><br>Your mind clears<br>Your mind clears<br>Your mind clears</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Reed Stormwind</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Kedge keep is awesome and fun. I would recommend hitting it when you reach 30. It is very safe. You cannot solo but with a small group you can get a ton of xp. In the 30's you are limited to the entrance of Kedge fighting the Lancer Swordfish which spawn there. They are around level 30 each. Problem is finding people adventurous enough to check it out, as Bandolo illustrates. They think it is a 40+ zone. They are quite mistaken. I have taken likey 20 people into Kedge and all of them Love it. It is different and fun. I get tells all the time from these people asking if I am in there and wanting to go back. Use Enduring Breath and keep our Water Breathing song as a back up. Getting an EB is no prob as Rangers often are your Groupmates as they want the RainCaller. Expect no loot. Kedge in the 30's is XP only. Our Stamina Song is awesome there for once. You can purchase unlimited Fish Scales for Enduring Breath in East Commons at the last inn leading to West commons.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Lake of Ill Omen</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=World Zone</font>|<font size="1">Tag=lakeofillomen</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>TEOLEN</b> (<i>2/7/02</i>) Lots of people say that once you ding 30 that you should head straight to Frontier Mountains or Overthere. Don't listen. The hands-down fastest way to get from 27-32 (almost everything goes light blue at 32) is to charm kite every blue con you see in LOIO. You will average 1/2 blue per kill, mobs don't hit too hard, no casters, and it's less work on the wrists than DoT kiting. It is true that you can get more exp per kill in FM charming brutes, about 3/4 blue per kill, but it is harder to pull efficiently and mobs hit a lot harder there. I found that I spent more time recovering from kites gone bad than getting kills, so LOIO still remains on top. If all the constant blabbering in /ooc is annoying you, just turn it off. Things become peaceful then.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Torfin</b> (<i>11/20/01</i>) I have found that your first hell level, 30, is quite a slow one. Not hard but just slow. My best advice for Bards in LOIO is not to group unless you suck at kiting/fear kiting/chram kiting. With the following strategy i leveled from 30-31 in about 4 hours. <br><br> First off, set up your song hotkeys with 1) Selos, 2) Hymn, 3) Jons Whistling Warsong, 4) Bellow, 5) Solons Song of the Sirens, 6) Selos Consonant Chain, 7) Fufil's, 8) Invis or Fear, 9) /pet attack, 10) /pet target. <br><br>Then, make sure you have your drum in hand and head towards the mill. From the mill, go to the Skeleton Ruins where the higher end MoBs are. The, facing the ruins, take a left and run up the hill till you go down into another ravine/valley. Then, take a right through the mountains onto a long stretch of flat land. Keep running straight until you see a big weird looking ruin. Inside of it lay 5 or 6 Goblins. The flat area to the left side of the ruins will be your kiting grounds.<br><br>Make sure you have about 5-8 minutes to spare to kite them. If the phone rings, do not answer it. If there is a knock on the door dont even blink. This process needs your full attention because even a small mistake and you will get hit by about 6 HIGHLY pissed off goblins.<br><br>That said, start off with drum in hand and selos for a tick, then charm the highest con goblin(warlord). Then press F8 and then press 9 on your numpad for you pet to attack that gob. The entir pack should beat the living bjesus out of the warlord until charm wears off. After you press F8, press 10 to target your pet. Then, when they rush you, either start twisting Selos, Fufil's and Bellow on him till he dies or charm him for another round. With the higher cons, you can usually have them stand up for 2 rounds, then finish it with a kite. Then, target another gobby of the pack and do the same with it. Keep doing this until you have 1 MoB left. Melee the snot out of that by either twisting Hymn,Warsong,Chains or Fear,Chains,Warsong. <br><br>After this, you should have about 5 or 6 bodies to loot, and about 1-2 blues of exp. Then, heal up if you were hit by the pack or last gobby and start doing regular charm kiting on the passing MoBs or swarm kite them/swarm charm kite them again. All in all, if you have a good hour or so, you can usually keep the pack going for about 20 mins because there is no real competition over there and MANY MoBs wander there. The spawn time on the Gobs is about 10-15 mins, so they are a steady, safe source of exp if you need to take breaks in between kills.<br><br>This strategy is very effective for many other places most notably OT, DL, IC, EW, and CC. The exp is faster because it takes less time to kill every MoB and you get full exp each time. VERY efficient. You can use this strategy until about 33 in LOIO and then apply it elsewhere.<br><br>Hope this Helps someone in hell. = )<br><br>Torfin<br>31'st note of the symphony<br>Bertoxxulous</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Debarker Foreverquestin</b> (<i>10/22/01</i>) I came back to LOIO after finishing my 30 hell in HHK which took Less than a day. I found that those (myself) that never really learned how to fear/kite and only learned to bellow DoT and Chain were safer here and the exp is about a half blue to a 3rd of a blue if you finally want to solo from 31 to 33 and the loot isnt really all that bad its not great but it adds up, i like to kill giants just like the next bard but we all learn our own way and for those that dont kite try war boned skels, sarnaks, and goblin warriors and you will LVL from 31 to 34 in 4 or 5 days at 4 hours a day.<br>Find me on vazaelle and i'll help you out.<br></span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Rivan Runeblade</b> (<i>9/6/01</i>) I came back to here at lvl 34 and tried my hand at Bloodgills, my guild said I was crazy but i tried it anyways... after a few of Kiting they dropped like flies.. =) ... both of the ones i killed were yellow to me.  the spawn under the Astral Projection i believe is only a 2 spawn ... i just used Selo's and the Target DoT... *forgot name atm*..  really good exp and if you havent gotten yer Lake of Ill Omen coin yet they always drop them.  Safe hunting to you all.<br><br>Rivan Runeblade<br>34 Bard Dark Elf<br>Amalgam of Force</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Githoniel Weavesong</b> (<i>6/16/01</i>) Another place to Fear kite in LoIO is the goblin caves.  If you get down to the zone for Warslik Woods (use the entrance NOT at the end of the road from Sarnak Keep and stay