b>Ridil</b> (<i>11/7/01</i>) I've seen posts that the NPC for Emerald Cloak of the Faydark quest no longer spawns, therefore no cloak.  Haven't checked it out yet - anyone know for sure?  &quot;Say it ain't so!&quot;</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Rhymmer Chordcaller</b> (<i>6/12/01</i>) OK, I know Lesser Fay has a bad rep.  Well, that's a blessing in disguise for us.  I went here at 32 to get the two new quest items (Gilded Silver Skull earring and Emerald Cloak of the Faydark).  No XP for the Earring MoBs (frightlings at the pixie tower, approximately p1200, p2700) but killer XP for the Cloak.  <br>     The fairy village has been corrupted.  This is the mushroom village at approximately p1100, p3600, the place has Gearheart at the center of the village.  There is a hill with a tree to the East of the village, just orient your self so you are looking at Gearheart's face and you can see all 5 guard spawn points.  DON'T get too close to the village, unless you like eating harm touches for 161-181 from annoying green MoBs, the Undead Sprite Horrors.  Basically all you want to attack are the Undead Sprite Guards and Bloodboil.  At 32-35th levels the guards and BB were blue to me and until 35th level every 2-3 guards gave me a blue bub of XP.  You can use lull to split the 4 outer guards, they ring the village one at each compass point (N, E, W, and S).  The center guard, to the right of Gearheart if you are facing him, is the placeholder for Bloodboil.  The guards seem to be on an approximate 17 minute timer.  So if you split the spawn well, you have about 3 minutes between each pop once it is broken,<br>          OK, the Item you need for the Cloak is Bloodboil's broken wing.  Bloodboil is a high 20's-low30's SK.  Has a harm touch for 271 then likes to try to fear and clinging dark you.  Notice I said tries, in 16 kills he only feared me once.  He also tends to run if you chant kite him below 33% HPs, but he doesn't run if you melee.<br>    Melee?  Yep. :)  Here's the bonus for this area.  All the guards are basic warrior types, but you can solo melee them at 32.  I could usually handle 2, by using instill doubt to &quot;ping pong&quot; them, i.e. melee one and keep hitting ID until it ran, then switch to the second and melee and ID it until it ran, by then the first was back, rinse, lather and repeat.  In the 3 days I was there, my defense went from 130ish to 157, my offense maxed, I was able to keep dual wield and slash maxed, work up  piercing from 70ish to 150, and bash from 20ish to 57 (still have to work on bash).<br>    There are only a few dangers in the area.  Thistlefoot spawns near the village and he's mean, just ignore him and he should ignore you.  There are occasional wandering horrors and even though they are green, the WILL agro and attack which means a harm touch for 150-180.  In over 20 hours there, I never saw a brownie scout.  However, there is a new mob, Equestrielle the Corrupted.  She's a mean SK, 401 harm touch hits fast for 60-80 damage, life taps for 25 and all the other nasty SK stuff.  Equestrielle CAN keep up with Selo's, so make sure to equip a drum to outrun her.  The Mistmoore zone line is almost due south from the mushroom village so you can flee there to clear aggro (yeah, I know it seems weird to run TO Mistmoore for safety).<br>     The goodies: most guards carry from 5 gold to 3 plat.  About 50% have fine steel weapons and about 25% have medium range gems and jewelry (pearls, topaz, mithril earrings, jade earrings), plus some have lesser gems and words/runes.  In about 5 hours I could get half way through a level and collect enough coin and loot to get about 100pp.<br>     The songs I used: Kelin's Lugubrious Lament (level 8), Hymn of Restoration (level 6), Selo's Accelerando (level 5), Melanie's Mellifluous Motion (level 21), Selo's Consonant Chain (level 23), Fufil's Curtailing Chant (level 30), Jonathan's Whistling Warsong (level 7), and Alenia's Disenchanting Melody (level 22).  I used hymn, chain and warsong for melee; accelerando and Fufil's for kiting; and Melanie's and Alenia's for emergencies (some of the wanderer's along the route to the mushroom village like to DoT and root/ensnare).<br></span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Lord Nagafen's Lair</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=soldunb</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Phrank Sinnatra</b> (<i>6/28/02</i>) Go to Bugs & Bats and take a right down past the lava to a hallway right before the lava beetle spawn and the path to the efreeti lair. We used to call it the fear hall. If you sing ae snare and fear the mobs run back and forth along this small stretch of hall. Very very nice xp to be had.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Nurgh</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Nagafen's Lair (SolB): Was good grouping from 35 up to 40 or so, in the window room alone. Indoors, so no selo's, but it has numerous egress points (either to Lavastorm or Solusek's Eye (SolA)) so escaping if things go bad, is not too bad. Loot is ok (large bronze/fine steel) and there are merchants just outside in Lavastorm. Loot is better in other spots in SolB, but escape from those is a bit more difficult and trains can get dangerous. Usually packed, and can be hard to get a group (lists! Ack!)</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td colspan="2" nowrap><b>Lower Guk</b>&nbsp;<font size="1">Type=Dungeon</font>|<font size="1">Tag=gukbottom</font></td><td align="right" valign="top">|</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Caylan Shadowblayes</b> (<i>8/22/02</i>) I died 6 times getting my mask here with my guild at lvl 28, which included the help of a 54 mage and a 51 shaman. I got my arse whupped,