 grouping bard in the Rathe Mountains, I recommend using Angstlich's and Chain combo.  This is assuming you are hunting the various &quot;giant&quot; mobs out there.  <br><br> Using this tactic, I was able to keep a  giants damage to about 300-500points during a battle depending on resists, and did not build up as much Hate as one would imagine.<br><br>CAVEAT<br><br> The Rathe Mountains are now a LOT harder to charm kite giants, since, I believe a patch must have changed our charm spell.<br><br> I have noticed that once our charm spell sticks, our target will not re aggro his previous opponent.  We must retarget and /pet attack. . . .or . . . take the dreaded 78 points of damage punch to get your pet to jump in.<br><br>  Even in &quot;beauty&quot; mode with charisma gear on (cha 143),  it takes MUCH more work and is MUCH more dangerous to attempt this.  <br><br>Just makes things a bit more interesting in the always interesting life of a bard. :)<br><br>Kyepez 33 bard<br><br>Kyepez plays a little Manilow<br><br>Your Mind Clears<br>Your Mind Clears<br>Your Mind Clears</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Trewayn Fifate (Drinal)</b> (<i>4/6/01</i>) Once you hit 30 make sure your CHA is as high as you can get it and charm kite Hill Giants.  By this time, if you have followed the guides on EQDiva, you should have an almost complete set of lambent armor.  Add in a splitpaw tooth necklace, Enchanted Electrum Fire Ruby rings and, if you are lucky enough to find one, a Mask of Deception from LGuk (pick it up while you're putting the Lambent Breastplate together) and you will end up with a CHA in the mid to high thirties.<br><br>At lvl 30 there is no single HG that can always resist you with a CHA this high.  You will get a lot of resistances, don;t get me wrong, but the mobs will remember their previous targets so just back off with Selo and charm kite away.  If you can find an enchanter in the zone, ask for a CHA buff and watch tho