et about fear kiting either (another good strategy if there isn't anything to charm)!From the North karana zone, the spires can be located directly due north of the stone bridge. Past the spires, you will find the aviak village (where theres a vendor who will sell to you if you sneak behind him). From the Lake Rathe zone, the aviak village is South/Southwest, and from the aviak village, the spires are north. Another bonus about hunting here, is that the arena zone, highkeep/highpass, and Split Paw (which is REALLY close) are located near the zone so as to make CRs and zoning away from monsters easier. Also, this zone can be gotten to by basically aynone. Just look at maps and whatnot for way to get there. Enjoi South Karana!</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Durwind</b> (<i>8/15/01</i>) I tried camping the Gnolls in a group, and found the exp to be dismal.  After shouting for a camp check several times and even asking specifically if the hill was camped, I found a nice spot just north of the Gnoll Hill and settled in.  There are two gnolls that spawn on a little flat spot there.  One will sit there until pulled, the other runs immediately after spawning.  They are both on about a 5 or 6 minute timer, so if you break it right, it is good steady experience until level 35.  It would only take about a minute or two to chain/fear kite these guys (at level 33) leaving plenty of time to rest and heal up for the next one.  If the north spire group was weak, you would occasionally get the pair that spawns there for you to charm kite.  If one of the spire groups was very strong, they would sometimes try to grab my spawn thinking it was an escapee from another spire.  I found that some groups didnt even know there was a spawn spot there.  Most groups would leave me alone if I explained that the hill was camped.  (If not, there was always charm pulling.)  Not bad loot either considering the FS Weapons, Split Paw Armor and the Gem In