30. For a while, I stayed away from charming Stonegazer Cockatrices and Sarnak Knights for fear they would be too high level for my song. But after some experimentation, I found that most of the time they were quite susceptible to my charms. :) Admittedly, a lot of resists, but if you get your CHA up there (mine is at 156 with all my CHA gear on) it works well.<br><br>The greatest thing about the Overthere for charm kiting is the variety of mobs.  You want to charm a mob of a different type than the one you want to kill, so they'll automatically remember who to attack when you re-charm them. With 5 different varieties, it's possible to charm-kite non-stop for 4, 6, 8, or more mobs. Just as your target dies, look around. There's probably another suitable target nearby. I remember once I started a charm-kite just as dusk was falling in the game. When I finally killed my last creature, the sun was coming up. Half a yellow bubble of XP in Hell Level 30. <br><br>Words of caution: Some Sarnak Knights move at SOW speed, and will outrun you without your drum. Pick on the Knights that move at a normal pace. Also, you can usually outrun rhinos without your drum, provided you aren't weighted down. When you get within 8-10 stone of your max weight, avoid the rhinos or just swap out your flute for your drum.<br><br>Excellent XP and decent loot. Cockatrices especially are good for a few plat each. Highly recommended.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Lenadas</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) I moved to OT at 35, but I regret not going sooner. Looking back I'd go there at about 30 or 31.</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><span class="clsSmall"><li type="square"><b>Kocho Divah</b> (<i>3/2/01</i>) Watch out for goons (level 50+ dragoons who will wipe you out so quickly you don't know what hit you, if you have your Mask of Deception, definitely don it here! I suggest not fighting on the popular &quot;ledge&quot; next to Frontier Mountain zone, as the goons are often trained there. I like to stick near the tower on the southeast part of zone. Its level there and also a steady stream of sarnaks and mobs.<br><br>
